&lt;p&gt;The Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust has an international reputation for high quality patient care, education and research and its partnership with the Institute of Cancer Research has created the largest comprehensive cancer centre in Europe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Clinical Research Fellow post which is available for 12 months. The post has been established to support research and clinical duties within the Department. Extensive experience will be gained from trial design and management of phase I to III clinical trials. Translational research can be facilitated at the Institute of Cancer Research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based in the Gynaecology Research Unit which operates at both the Sutton and Chelsea sites of the Royal Marsden Hospital. In order to fulfil the responsibilities of this post you must be eligible for full GMC registration and have medical or clinical oncology experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Susana Banerjee, Consultant Medical Oncologist via e-mail on Susana.Banerjee@rmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
